Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Atomic Energy Community, and in particular Articles 47 and 50 thereof,
Having regard to the proposal from the Commission,
Whereas, by Decision 74/295/Euratom (1), the Council established the joint undertaking Hochtemperatur-Kernkraftwerk GmbH (HKG);
Whereas on 11 July 1983 the general meeting of the joint undertaking decided to increase the company's subscribed capital;
Whereas this increase calls for an amendment to the Statutes of the joint undertaking;
Whereas such an amendment does not affect the provisions governing the joint undertaking and is consistent with the development of the project;
Whereas such an amendment should therefore be approved,
